4️ API Flow Example

Register API Flow

POST /api/v1/auth/register
        │
        ▼
authRoutes.js
        │
        ▼
registerController()
        │
        ▼
userModel.js
        │
        ▼
MongoDB → users collection
        │
        ▼
Response sent to client




Login API Flow

POST /api/v1/auth/login
        │
        ▼
authRoutes.js
        │
        ▼
loginController()
        │
        ▼
Check user in MongoDB
        │
        ▼
Password match
        │
        ▼
Return response




Get User API Flow

GET /api/v1/user/getUser
        │
        ▼
userRoutes.js
        │
        ▼
getUserController()
        │
        ▼
Return user data




5️ Server Flow (server.js)

Your server.js acts like the main entry point.

Flow:

Start Server
     │
     ▼
Load Environment Variables (.env)
     │
     ▼
Connect MongoDB Database
     │
     ▼
Initialize Express App
     │
     ▼
Load Middleware
   ├── cors
   ├── express.json()
   └── morgan
     │
     ▼
Load Routes
   ├── /api/v1/test
   ├── /api/v1/auth
   └── /api/v1/user
     │
     ▼
Server Listening on PORT 9000



